  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2.40.1\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n\r\n```\r\n      erigon --datadir=/opt/data\r\n             --chain=goerli\r\n             --authrpc.port=8551\r\n             --authrpc.vhosts=*\r\n             --authrpc.jwtsecret=/opt/data/jwtsecret\r\n             --externalcl\r\n             --http.vhosts=*\r\n             --http.corsdomain=*\r\n             --torrent.download.rate=100mb\r\n             --http.api=eth,debug,net,web3,trace,erigon\r\n```\r\n\r\nChain/Network: Goerli\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI’d expect that the JS tracer context objects would contain block and transaction hashes. See relevant code: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/eth/tracers/js/goja.go#L149-L155\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThose properties aren’t set.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nTracer code:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{\r\n   callstack: [{}],\r\n   fault: function(log, db) {},\r\n   result: function(ctx, db) {\r\n      return ctx\r\n   },\r\n   enter: function(frame) {\r\n   },\r\n   exit: function(frameResult) {\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNo block/tx hash is returned for any block (recent or old) \r\n",
